<HEADLINE>
ASIA PACIFIC BROADBAND ELECTS NEW INTERIM CHAIRWOMAN
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan.  25 (CNA) 01/26/07  10:53:30 (By Y.C. Jou)
</P>
<P>
Four remaining managing directors of the crisis-ridden Asia
Pacific Broadband Telecom (APBT) Thursday voted Wang Lin-mei,
general manager of China Rebar, as the company's interim
chairwoman.
</P>
<P>
Former APBT Chairwoman Wang Chin Shih-ying, Wang's stepmother, is
now on the run in the United States on insider trading and
embezzlement charges.  Former APBT Vice Chairman Wang Lin-tai,
half-brother of Wang Lin-mei, was held incommunicado Jan. 23 for
suspected irregular dealings of the company's assets, only four
days after being elected to serve as interim chairman, along with
two other high- ranking company officials.
</P>
<P>
Among the APBT's original managing directors, Wang Chin Shih-ying
and her husband Wang You-theng, founder of the Rebar Asia Pacific
Group, are wanted by the prosecution, three are detained and two
have resigned.
</P>
<P>
The government, which has intervened to assist the company sort
out its financial  troubles,  said however that the company's
operations remained largely normal.
</P>
<P>
The unlisted APBT has capitalization of NT$65.68 billion and
employs  more than 1,300  people.  It has suffered  financial
difficulties associated with the Rebar Group crisis.
</P>
